14.
Completion by Owner. Owner agrees with Bank and any subsequent holder of the
Note that in the event Contractor shall not complete said improvements in the manner and time
set out in said Plans and herein, Owner will promptly cause said improvements to be so
completed and will pay all costs of completing same and will pay all unpaid sums due and owing
on the Note according to the face, tenor, effect and reading thereof.
45. Alterations and Extras. No alterations shall be made in the work shown or
described by the Plans, nor shall any extra work or materials be charged or paid for, unless a
separate estimate for such extra work is submitted in writing by Contractor to Owner and agreed
to in writing by them before the extra work is started. The additional amount to be paid for all
extra work and materials so agreed to and furnished shall be a part of the indebtedness secured
by the liens created by this Contract. Bank, at its option and subject to the execution of such
additional loan documents as it might require, may advance all or part of such additional amount.
If Bank elects pot to advance such additional amount, Owner shall pay Contractor in cash upon
completion of such extra work and Contractor shall have a lien on the property for the payment
of such amount, which lien Contractor agrees shall be subordinate to the liens granted to
Contractor and transferred to Bank in this Contract. All extra work done, or material furnished,
without such agreement shall be considered as performed under the original Contract and no
extra pay shall be demanded or allowed.
16.
Receipts and Releases. Upon request from time to time, Contractor shall furnish
Owner or Bank proper receipts and releases from any and all subcontractors, workmen and
suppliers, so that no liens may be fixed upon the property except the express liens created by this
Contract and the lien of the Deed of Trust. "
17.
No Work Commenced! Contractor and Owner hereby warrant that no materials
have been furnished and no labor performed for the construction of the improvements at the time
of execution, acknowledgment and delivery hereof.
18.
Controlling Documents. Owner, Contractor and Bank have entered into the Tri-
Party Agreement simultaneously with the execution of this Contract. Any conflict or
inconsistency between the terms of said Tri-Party Agreement and this Contract shall be governed
and controlled by the Tri-Party Agreement. Any conflict or inconsistency between the terms of
this Contract and the Plans shall be governed and controlled by this Contract.
If Owner and Contractor have entered into a separate construction contract, then any
conflict between said separate construction contract, on the one hand, and this Contract or the
Tri-Party Agreement, on the other hand, shall be governed and controlled by this Contract and by
the Tri-Party Agreement.
19.
General Provisions.
(a)
This Contract, the Tri-Party Agreement and the Plans, insofar as they relate in any
part or in any way to the work hereunder, constitute the entire agreement between the parties
hereto, and it is expressly understood and agreed that there are no agreements or promises by and
between said parties, except as herein set forth.
